en_6123750_0	COLOMBO (News 1st)- Prime Minister Ranil Wickramasinghe will leave the country today (March 01) to attend ‘Invest Sri Lanka’ conference held in Singapore.
en_6123750_1	‘Invest Sri Lanka’ conference is organized by the Colombo Stock Exchange with the objective to promote foreign direct investments in Sri Lanka.
en_6123750_2	The Prime Minister is scheduled to speak at the conference tomorrow.
en_6123750_3	Some of the major investors in the region are scheduled to attend the conference which will be held at the at the Hotel Four Seasons in Singapore.
